<span id="freeTextContainer12409136902925315799">One of the best books I have read in a long time. Marivaux successfully explores the theme of class divide in the 18th century. Reading this in the original French is much better than English as you can really see the way in which he conveys the difference between servant and master in the way language is used. I won&apos;t spoil the ending, but I shall leave you to decide whether this shows that the class divide really has been bridged.</span>
  <span id="freeText12409136902925315799" style="display:none">One of the best books I have read in a long time. Marivaux successfully explores the theme of class divide in the 18th century. Reading this in the original French is much better than English as you can really see the way in which he conveys the difference between servant and master in the way language is used. I won't spoil the ending, but I shall leave you to decide whether this shows that the class divide really has been bridged.</span>
